The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent THE time has come for the Matabeleland region to shine at auditions of one of the most anticipated television series that will be broadcast on Zimpapers Television Network (ZTN). Auditions for the series’ cast are being conducted today and are underway at Amakhosi Theatre. The auditions are targeted at actors fluent isiNdebele aged between 25 and 60 years. Media personality, Tendai “Sokostina” Garwe who is the ZTN features director urged actors, including aspiring ones to come for the auditions in their numbers. <img class="alignnone wp-image-544664 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/ztn.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/ztn.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/ztn-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “We’re in Bulawayo today for auditions for the series. The auditions began at 9AM and are ongoing. I want to urge people to come in their numbers and try out. “Members of the public should note that Covid-19 regulations will be strictly followed at the auditions so as expected, people must come wearing masks,” said Sokostina. The series is expected to be filmed in the rural areas of Insiza district in Filabusi this month. “Yesterday we were in Filabusi where we meet the local leadership as we intend to shoot the production there.” ZTN which has been leading the way in terms of quality productions wants to have a wider reach in its storytelling prowess. – @mthabisi_mthire  